PN,37504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1781028676
OL,3,CNew council leader says Birmingham bin
OL,4,Cstrike firings would be 'sign of
OL,5,Cfailure'
OL,7,FThe comments come after former council
OL,8,Fleader John Cotton claimed senior
OL,9,Fcouncil officers and government-
OL,10,Fappointed commissioners had pushed to
OL,11,Fdismiss workers during negotiations
OL,12,Fover the dispute.
OL,14,FMr Cotton, who lost his seat in last
OL,15,Fmonth's local elections, said he had
OL,16,Frepeatedly resisted attempts to sack
OL,17,Fstaff instead of reaching a deal with
OL,18,FUnite the Union.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1781028676
OL,3,CNew council leader says Birmingham bin
OL,4,Cstrike firings would be 'sign of
OL,5,Cfailure'
OL,7,F"As leader, I consistently opposed
OL,8,Fthose forces who were pushing to
OL,9,Fdismiss our workforce, rather than
OL,10,Fnegotiate a solution," he said.
OL,12,FBirmingham City Council has denied
OL,13,Frecommending dismissals and insists no
OL,14,Fformal agreement had been reached to
OL,15,Fend the strike.
OL,17,FA council spokesperson said the
OL,18,Fauthority remained committed to
OL,19,Ffinding a "lawful, reasonable and
OL,20,Findustrially acceptable settlement".
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@VO]{D@KOU|D@cO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
