FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1781028676
OL,3,CNew council leader says Birmingham bin
OL,4,Cstrike firings would be 'sign of
OL,5,Cfailure'
OL,7,FMr Harmer confirmed he has not yet
OL,8,Fspoken directly to Unite since taking
OL,9,Fover the leadership on Friday.
OL,11,FThe political makeup of Birmingham
OL,12,FCity Council changed significantly
OL,13,Ffollowing the local elections, with no
OL,14,Fparty securing overall control.
OL,16,FDespite the Liberal Democrats being
OL,17,Fthe smallest group in the coalition,
OL,18,Fwith 12 councillors, Mr Harmer has
OL,19,Fbecome council leader with the backing
OL,20,Fof the Greens and a group of
OL,21,Findependents.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,376,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F375A1781028676
OL,3,CNew council leader says Birmingham bin
OL,4,Cstrike firings would be 'sign of
OL,5,Cfailure'
OL,7,FUnder the coalition agreement, the
OL,8,Fleadership is expected to rotate in
OL,9,Ftwo years, with Green Party leader
OL,10,FJulien Pritchard set to take over the
OL,11,Frole.
OL,13,FCllr Pritchard said: "We want a fair
OL,14,Fdeal for workers and this city.
OL,15,FDismissing workers is not something I
OL,16,Fwant to do. The strike going on
OL,17,Findefinitely like it has is not
OL,18,Facceptable."
OL,26,@uD@VOUzD@LO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/8
